Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.19,0:00:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,CHECK PLACEMENT Honestly.\NYou're such a troublemaker!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.69,0:00:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times are you\Ngoing to pretend to run away?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.40,0:00:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The next time you do it,\Nyou won't get dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.67,0:00:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand, Milosh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.10,0:00:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.27,0:00:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Take your hands out of your pockets\Nwhen you talk to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.30,0:00:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.07,0:00:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.11,0:00:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.14,0:00:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the blonde lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.04,0:00:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw her on\NDominican Street, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if she lives\Nin that area.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.98,0:00:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you follow her\Nall the way?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.02,0:00:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was hungry and\Nmy stomach was growling.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.15,0:00:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, we've got to find out where\Nthe lady is and turn her over to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.49,0:00:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer didn't\Nkill the director.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.99,0:00:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got to prove\Nhis innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.56,0:00:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Prove his innocence?\NWill that save Mr. Grimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.27,0:00:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! We're having\Na strategy meeting right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.54,0:00:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosh, hurry and eat your food.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.48,0:02:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the underground orphanage,\Nwhere the first incident occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.38,0:02:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone killed the former director\Nof 511 Kinderheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.35,0:02:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The children say that\Na blonde woman
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.52,0:02:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,walked passed them\Nright after the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.83,0:02:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He was conducting\Nan experiment here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.13,0:03:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the complete opposite of\Nwhat happened at 511 Kinderheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.43,0:03:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems he was experimenting\Nwith giving the children affection.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.24,0:03:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want to do?\NDo you want to go in?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.31,0:03:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The police probably stripped away\Nall the evidence already.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.54,0:03:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.81,0:03:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,"To Mr. Police Officer!\NMr. Grimmer is innocent."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.02,0:03:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,"To Mr. Detective!\NThe blonde lady is the killer."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.69,0:03:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's those children...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.42,0:03:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The orphanage children came back\Nand posted these up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.63,0:03:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,"To Mr. Grimmer..."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.74,0:03:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Milan Boucek. ..\NA card of a famous soccer player.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.01,0:03:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's valuable to the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.91,0:03:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I react?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.11,0:03:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of expression\Nshould I make in this situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.02,0:04:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,My emotions were taken\Nfrom me at 511 Kinderheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.26,0:04:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, I was taught various\Nemotional expressions at a strange school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.53,0:04:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But situations like this\Nare the most difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.24,0:04:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the right way\Nto react to this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.98,0:04:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you go and\Nsee those children?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.91,0:04:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Mr. Grimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.88,0:04:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I always hear things from\Nthe children about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.95,0:04:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The children are out playing.\NThey haven't come back yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.09,0:04:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If only they'd come back earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.13,0:04:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look! The children's journals...\NOr rather, a lot of letters written to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.40,0:04:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mr. Grimmer,\Nlet's play soccer again."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.91,0:04:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mr. Grimmer, I'll teach you how to play\Nsoccer since you're not very good at it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.14,0:04:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mr. Grimmer,\Nlet's all play together again."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.98,0:05:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm smiling right now, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.49,0:05:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.06,0:05:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned the form\Nof a smiling face.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.79,0:05:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm remaining in\Npeoples' memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.53,0:05:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why...do those children. ..\Ncare about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.00,0:05:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because they love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.44,0:05:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Love...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.91,0:05:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Before, when my son died,\NI was thinking of how I should react.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.62,0:05:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I cry in this situation?\NHow long should I cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.96,0:05:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I scream,\Nor should I clench my teeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.93,0:05:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now,\NI still don't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.44,0:05:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.51,0:06:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.11,0:06:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Antonio.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.72,0:06:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer, bad news!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.58,0:06:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Antonio?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.09,0:06:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We got word from the kids at\NCeske Orphanage ! I-It's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.12,0:06:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down, Antonio. Calm\Ndown and tell me what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.83,0:06:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They found the blonde lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.06,0:06:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday,\Nwe all kept watch to find her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.17,0:06:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, Milosh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.40,0:06:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosh disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.81,0:06:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,CHECK PLACEMENT I see. The\Npeople who have come to see you were
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.32,0:06:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a middle-aged gentleman,\Na tall German man,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.82,0:06:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and a long-haired\NJapanese man?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.32,0:06:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.09,0:06:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you may have forgotten\Nanother person who came to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.53,0:06:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the nurse, a long-haired\Nblonde woman came to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.50,0:07:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Woman? No.\NA woman never came.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.54,0:07:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the nurse was sure.\NShe was very beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.25,0:07:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, very beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.92,0:07:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.29,0:07:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.12,0:07:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.86,0:07:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.13,0:07:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Have we met somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.40,0:07:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.07,0:07:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.10,0:07:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.57,0:07:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.84,0:07:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You walk around this area often,\Ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.38,0:07:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.45,0:07:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.82,0:07:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Umm. .. My mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.39,0:07:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't just stand there.\NWhy don't you have a seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.49,0:07:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.29,0:08:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm.. .\NAre you going to move?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.80,0:08:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.03,0:08:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you have a big bag.\NAnd there's nothing in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.78,0:08:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is your mother somewhere\Naround here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.48,0:08:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.31,0:08:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you were looking for\Nyour mother, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.58,0:08:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But I don't know if\Nshe's around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.96,0:08:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how will you find her? Do\Nyou have her picture or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.09,0:08:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.93,0:08:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you won't know her face.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.56,0:08:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll know! I'll know my mom\Nwhen I see her face!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.00,0:08:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No one at the orphanage\Nbelieves me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.10,0:08:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone says that\NI won't be able to tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.87,0:08:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'll know my mom\Nwhen I see her!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.84,0:08:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.34,0:08:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.94,0:08:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom will know me\Nwhen she sees me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.59,0:09:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you find her, what if she\Nacts as if she doesn't know you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.86,0:09:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.39,0:09:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you born because\Nyou were wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.03,0:09:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why were you abandoned?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.40,0:09:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't your mother abandon you\Nbecause she hated you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.78,0:09:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.91,0:09:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing special\Nabout being born.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.32,0:09:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.52,0:09:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the universe is "death."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.92,0:09:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to the universe, the lives created\Non Earth are short and insignificant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.96,0:09:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Death is normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.47,0:09:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So why live?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.87,0:09:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it because\Nsomeone wanted you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.94,0:09:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wanted you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.32,0:10:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your reason for living?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.49,0:10:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A beautiful,\Nlong-haired blonde woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.59,0:10:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that would be Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.59,0:10:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Anna!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.49,0:10:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this woman, Anna,\Nlive around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.76,0:10:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I believe she lives\Nin the apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.67,0:10:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,at the end of the dead-end street\Ntwo corners down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.40,0:10:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she's a very nice girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.81,0:10:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She's good-natured\Nand always greets me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.11,0:10:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna? Yes, yes,\Nshe's a nice girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.62,0:10:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She always calls out\Nto me with a smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.18,0:10:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know which room\Nand which floor she lives on?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.79,0:10:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.36,0:10:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That window on the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.29,0:10:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If what the children said is true...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.20,0:10:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And... If it's true that\Nthat woman kidnapped Milosh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.73,0:10:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If that woman, Anna, who's living here\Nis the same one we're looking for, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.51,0:11:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that woman is\Nthe person I think she is,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.01,0:11:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,everything will end now,\Nright here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.33,0:11:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She got away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.77,0:11:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did Milosh go?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.31,0:11:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Was he captured?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.48,0:11:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He was following that blonde woman\Nto prove my innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.98,0:11:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.62,0:11:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I react\Nin this situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.96,0:11:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Those children got involved in this because\Nthey were trying to prove my innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.20,0:12:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The children told you that Milosh\Nusually walks around Prague
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.40,0:12:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in search of his mother,\Ndidn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.57,0:12:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to meet\Nhis mother, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.65,0:12:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't feel anything\Nwhen my own son died.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.99,0:12:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, a female coworker\Nfrom the newspaper company
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.72,0:12:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,where I worked spoke to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.89,0:12:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She told me that she loved me.\NI married her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.50,0:12:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I was told that I wouldn't be suspected of\Nconducting spy activities if I was married.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.07,0:12:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,She got pregnant\Nand she had a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.11,0:12:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, my wife went shopping\Nnot far from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.31,0:12:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When I went into\Nmy son's room,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.78,0:12:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,he was lying down flat\Nand wasn't breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.18,0:12:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I applied artificial respiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.69,0:12:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time,\NI called the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.22,0:12:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I did everything I should have done.\NPerfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.69,0:13:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.30,0:13:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,At the funeral,\Nmy wife raged at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.07,0:13:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"How can you stay so calm?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.34,0:13:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"How can you not cry?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.41,0:13:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"You're always,\Nalways like that."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.04,0:13:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,"You were like that\Nwith me, too."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.15,0:13:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,"You can't love people."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.38,0:13:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"There's nothing\Nin your heart."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.08,0:13:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then my wife left.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.26,0:13:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to find Milosh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.93,0:13:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You said that Milosh was\Nthe child of a prostitute
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.90,0:13:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,from a red-light district near\Nthe Czech border, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.47,0:13:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.73,0:13:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If the person that was here,\Nis the person I think she is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.47,0:13:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think they'll\Nlet the boy live!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.58,0:13:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But they won't just kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.31,0:13:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The person\NI'm thinking of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.08,0:13:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,would probably kill him after\Ndoing the cruelest thing possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.19,0:14:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Germany is straight this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.50,0:14:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is my mom along\Nthe way there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.70,0:14:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lively place\Nup ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.97,0:14:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I can meet my mom, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.54,0:14:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll wait here.\NYou go on alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.24,0:14:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll know who your mother is\Nif you see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.94,0:14:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And your mother will know\Nwho you are if she sees you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.31,0:14:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But if no one calls out to you, that\Nmeans that you weren't wanted by anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.22,0:14:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.06,0:14:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.66,0:14:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.01,0:14:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.11,0:15:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Cruel, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.43,0:15:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.30,0:15:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.24,0:15:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.07,0:15:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking for who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.04,0:15:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.44,0:16:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mom?!\NThis is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.01,0:16:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.98,0:16:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know your mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.62,0:16:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.62,0:16:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?! Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.45,0:16:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.12,0:16:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the ones I know. ..\Nthere are about 50!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.23,0:16:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why were you abandoned?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.54,0:16:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.84,0:16:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Kid, Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.88,0:16:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you, Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.44,0:16:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.98,0:16:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm.. .\NI'm...looking for my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.32,0:16:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just let me hold you like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.78,0:16:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with that kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.39,0:16:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not your kid, is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.76,0:16:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.56,0:16:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't make mistakes like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.50,0:16:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You get diseases, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.70,0:17:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up! Want to fight?!\NCome on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.94,0:17:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.31,0:17:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.77,0:17:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on. No!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.54,0:17:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.78,0:17:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I paid you. I'm a customer.\NDo as your customer says!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.21,0:17:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.88,0:17:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! A child's watching!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.39,0:17:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.02,0:17:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch. Don't run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.83,0:17:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a teacher in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.93,0:17:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,At school, I'm a gentleman who's\Nhighly praised by parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.97,0:17:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and a wonderful teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.81,0:17:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a wonderful teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.52,0:17:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.22,0:17:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who wanted you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.82,0:17:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Kid... Money...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.66,0:18:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sick, Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.53,0:18:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm.. .I'm going to die soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.40,0:18:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.44,0:18:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, didn't I?\NI'm going to die soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.04,0:18:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Gimme money.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.47,0:18:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I only have this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.62,0:18:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Most of the universe is death.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.99,0:18:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who wanted you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.06,0:18:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What's your reason for living?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.58,0:18:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.19,0:19:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.00,0:19:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The red-light district\Nends around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.47,0:19:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There are several people in town\Nwho have seen Milosh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.24,0:19:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we turn back?\NHe still might be in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.82,0:19:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.80,0:19:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.73,0:19:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.84,0:19:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Now come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.61,0:20:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You tried your best to clear\Nmy name, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.59,0:20:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right now.\NCome here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.71,0:20:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.58,0:20:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this good, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.99,0:20:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it be better if I cried?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.66,0:20:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I was never taught. ..\Nsuch a difficult emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.78,0:21:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Milosh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.89,0:21:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you see?\NWhat have you seen?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.49,0:21:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you find out?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.20,0:21:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosh. .. Listen to me.\NYou have no mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.87,0:21:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But... But...\NYou were born for a reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.04,0:21:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You were born because\Nsomeone wanted you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.82,0:21:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Definitely...\NSomeone definitely wanted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.96,0:21:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Definitely...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.87,0:22:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Dr. Tenma.\NI'm not wrong, am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.52,0:22:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.48,0:22:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What expression. ..\Ndo I have...right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.56,0:22:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're crying.
